cancelOrders(bytes32[]).details: Cancels multiple orders by their order keys.

params.orderKeys: The array of order keys to cancel.

editOrders((bytes32,(uint8,uint8,address.details: newOrder's saleKind, side, maker, and nft must match the corresponding order of oldOrderKey, otherwise it will be skipped; only the price can be modified.newOrder's expiry and salt can be regenerated.

params.editDetails: The edit details of oldOrderKey and new order info

returns.newOrderKeys: The unique id of the order is returned in order, if the id is empty, the corresponding order was not edit correctly.

eip712Domain().details: returns the fields and values that describe the domain separator used by this contract for EIP-712 signature.

getOrders(address,uint256,uint8,uint8,ui.details: Retrieves a list of orders that match the specified criteria.

params.collection: The address of the NFT collection.
params.count: The maximum number of orders to retrieve.
params.firstOrderKey: The key of the first order to retrieve.
params.price: The maximum price of the orders to retrieve.
params.saleKind: The type of sale (fixed price or auction).
params.side: The side of the orders to retrieve (buy or sell).

returns.nextOrderKey: The key of the next order to retrieve.
returns.resultOrders: An array of orders that match the specified criteria.

makeOrders((uint8,uint8,address,(uint256.details: If Side=List, you need to authorize the EasySwapVault contract first (creating a List order will transfer the NFT to the order pool).If Side=Bid, you need to pass {value}: the price of the bid (similarly, creating a Bid order will transfer ETH to the order pool).order.maker needs to be msg.sender.order.price cannot be 0.order.expiry needs to be greater than block.timestamp, or 0.order.salt cannot be 0.

returns.newOrderKeys: The unique id of the order is returned in order, if the id is empty, the corresponding order was not created correctly.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

editOrders((bytes32,(uint8,uint8,address.notice: Cancels multiple orders by their order keys.

makeOrders((uint8,uint8,address,(uint256.notice: Create multiple orders and transfer related assets.
